name: NSPrintOperation.RenderingQuality
desc: Constants that specify the print quality in use.

items.name: case best
items.desc: Renders the printing at the best possible quality, regardless of speed.

items.name: case responsive
items.desc: Sacrifices the least possible amount of rendering quality for speed to maintain a responsive user interface. This option should be used only after establishing that best quality rendering does indeed make the user interface unresponsive.
